@node HISTORY "History"
---<History>---


Please also see the @{"What's New" Link NEW} Section....


                    Versions with NO version number ;-)
                    -----------------------------------

  All versions before v1.0 have been "Internal" releases sent via
  the SYSOP section on Fluffy-Net, Timm Rutland and Ben Dover had the VERY
  1st version would only access "CD0:", and could only show the first 128
  entries of Directorys.  It also couldn't flag - so you had to download 
  files one at a time.  For some bizzare reason - CD's with HUGE names also 
  don't like being "DIR"'ed - so sometimes, it would fail to download files 
  which where quite clearly there.


                     Version 1.0 (1st PUBLIC release)
                     --------------------------------

  1. I finally tracked down a very annoying bug whereby when you used the
  "Page" keys, all the information was corrupt (variables - the scurge of 
  my life). So hopefully this version is relatively BUG FREE (Hurrah!!).

  2. There are a couple of instances whereby this door will fail to download
  your selected file:  I have a CD where some of the filenames include 
  spaces in them such as "Barbie Girl" and "Battle Star" - it WILL download 
  entries like this but CANNOT download entries whereby there are spaces 
  AFTER the last word in the filename ie "Barbie Girl ".  Then again - 
  neither can KewlCDPro (Sorry Steve - but I DID check... maybe I'm wrong
  though...).

  If it does find one of these files - you will notice you get a nice "FILE
  NOT ONLINE" message quickly flash off screen.

  3. Also the same CD (a MOD collection CD from Finland) has one VERY 
  strange entry "AC/DC" - yup, a directory with a "/" character in it.  
  Basically, the door CANNOT even get inside this drawer (try it with 
  Directory Opus, this can't do it either).  So all in all, I think it's 
  pretty water tight.

  4. I altered the DOWNLOAD routine to COPY the file from CD to
  "BBS:Tempfiles", then download it from there.  Don't ask why, but this has
  vastly increased the programs ability to get files off the CD!! (It copys
  your MARKED files list over ONE AT A TIME - downloads them, then DELETES
  them from the drawer...)



             Version 1.0.1 (PRIVATE release for Timm Rutland)
             ------------------------------------------------

  If anyone other than Timm has this copy, then I'd be very suprised, do a
  VERSION check - and you can tell :-)

  1. No bug fixes, just altered it so it DID NOT read from line 0 of the
  Maxsbbs.config.  

  Turns out his SYSOP name isn't what appears in LINE 0 of his CONFIG (he's
  on the run from mad autograph hunters, who tracked him down after a couple
  of his proggys won the reader award in Amiga Format....)



                     Version 1.1 (2nd PUBLIC release)
                     --------------------------------

  1. Fixed a bug whereby if you tried to use the ENTER directory feature in
  a directory with NO sub-directorys, it would bitch and moan :-)

  2. Changed the ">" and "<" pointers for some seriously cool ANSI colours -
  you can now see much clearer which directory and file you are looking at

  3. Added LOCAL download to selected directory for LOCAL logins (rather 
  than the usual xxx-MODEM requester boxout...).  This swine took the 
  longest to figure out, as I didn't realise I had to put a "=" at the end 
  of the door call :-) [Appologies to Steve Clack for my MANY, MANY messages
  on the topic via Fluffynet just before I read the MaxPro DOC file]  
  What can I say?  It's a Max Pro bug - not a bug in my code - Hurrah!!


                     Version 1.2 (3rd PUBLIC release)
                     --------------------------------

  1. Ahem - still LOTS of bugs in the PAGE forwards, and reverse options of
  both the DIRECTORYS and FILES. Sorted these out ONCE AND FOR ALL ;-) 

  2. Stopped the program "going offscreen" if you attempted to go past the
  bottom of either the DIRECTORY or FILE listing once you where NOT on the
  first page of info (a real swine to sort out... lots of maths checking)

  2.1 Stopped the program "going offscreen" if you attempted to go back UP
  past the 1st item if you where NOT on the first page of info (same trouble
  as 2. to fix) - eventually, sorted it out.

  3. Not a bug-fix, just a major shrinking of the executable door code, I
  removed all my old PRINT STRING$(" ",80) and replaced them with the ANSI
  code to clear a line (much quicker, less compiled code) - I also told the
  AMOS compiler NOT to include the LIBRARY inside the program.  Regrettably,
  this means you will have to keep a copy of: AMOS.LIBRARY inside your LIBS:
  assign (I think everyone has it anyway)


  Fixed all of these the same night that I uploaded Version 1.1 to the
  Fluffynet (no patience me - always been my trouble)



                    Version 1.2.1 (4th PUBLIC release)
                    ----------------------------------

After MANY discussions with such notable Max experts as Steve Clack and
"Fosters" it was pointed out to me that using NODE numbers in the way I was
doing in 1.2 wasn't a VERY good idea because my door would CRASH and BURN
if remote users (ie, callers to the BBS) tried to access it.  So, I had to
find a way of knowing whether a user was REMOTE or LOCAL

    I tried using the KewlDoors "who typed key" - but it simply DOESN'T
WORK.  So - I altered the code to use the AMOSDOORS4MAXS extension by 
Ari Tsironis.  The routine he has made works PERFECTLY :-)

So - NO bug fixes really, apart from you can now SAFELY use this door on
your system (either Max PRO or Max 1.54) without it locking if users access
it.

Also - there is NO need for either a "+" (to indicate your system is
running Max Pro) or "=" (to indicate your system is running Max 1.54) after
the DRIVE identifer (ie FrillyCDPro CD0:)

Sorry about the number of updates within such a short space of time, but
this REALLY is a Max bug/feature - and I wasn't aware of it until my door
had been sent off.  Sadly - the feature I'm now using to discover whether
it was a LOCAL or REMOTE keypress means the door can now be used on MAX bbs
systems ONLY - It will NOT work on "Paragon" systems.



                    Version 1.2.2 (5th PUBLIC release)
                    ----------------------------------

1. Check to see if there is actually an object (ZIP disk,CD,H/D) present in
the device you are attempting to access.  Quite why I didn't do this from
day one - I really don't know - sorry to everyone about this VERY obvious
but never before spotted bug!!

2. Still a few nastys in the PAGE forwards/reverse code - re-wrote the
drive handling routine to CLEAR out any spurious data, so the problem
should be sorted.


                        Version 1.3b (BETA release)
                        ---------------------------

1. Total Re-write of the MARK files and DOWNLOAD section.  Ben Dover (Sysop
of Total Oblivion - NOW CLOSED) came up with a DAMN FINE idea.  When a file
is MARKED - it gets COPIED to "BBS:Tempfiles" immediately, when you UNMARK
it - it gets DELETED from "BBS:Tempfiles".  This saves lots of navigation
later on when it comes to download time (previous versions all COPIED the
marked filelist over at DOWNLOAD request time, one at a time).

2. This feature renders the use of the LOCALDOWNLOAD.DIR file useless
really, so DELETE the file from your FrillyCDPro drawer, as it is no longer
used.

3. Checked to see if "BBS:Tempfiles" exists, if it doesn't then it creates
it for you.

4. Constantly check (upon DIRECTORY entry, or PARENT access) to see if the
object you are accessing (CD/ZIP etc) is actually still present.  It was
possible to "crash" the door by removing the CD etc once the door was
running.  This cuts the chances of it doing so.

5. Tidied up the ANSI colours - so you can see if there are NO
FILES/DIRECTORIES (red background, white text), coloured the <MORE FILES>
and <MORE DIRECTORIES> bit in blue ansi, and coloured the DIRECTORY NAME,
and FILENAME bit in.

6. Cosmetic changes to the "centre" routine to allow for colours to be
passed to it.  Previously, it filtered them out by FORCING black background
and white text.

7. Re-write of the "wait for keypress" main routine to check whether the
caller is a REMOTE user, or a LOCAL SYSOP.  Remapped the cursor keys to
there "correct" values as reported LOCALLY

8. Changed the ESC key (previously used to go back to the PARENT directory)
to become the "P" key.  The ESC character (27) is used to determine if a
keypess is REMOTE or LOCAL. 

9.  Swapped BACK from the ARI "Amos" Maxs extension to KewlDoor Amos
extension.  Seemed a good idea at the time, it was simpler to detect the
remote users keypresses.


 
                                Version 1.4
                                -----------

1. Seperated the DIRECTORY and FILES display routines, so that when you
move up or down in either column, only the column you are navigating gets
"updated" on screen.  Results in a 50% speed increase for REMOTE users

2. Re-write of the routine to remove "extra" spaces at the end of
filenames.  

3. "Cosmetic" change.  Removed the "Instructions" and "Local Download"
screen to external ANSI files - purely in an attempt to keep the size of the
executable down.  

4. Re-wrote the CLEAR screen, and LOCATE routines, because KD CLEAR SCREEN
and KD LOCATE take up too much executable space, and aren't any faster than
simply either issuing an ANSI cursor position command, or doing a PRINT
CHR$(12).

5. Removed several bits of "redundant" code.  There was a few colour
setting commands which jumped straight into procedures which set the
colours themselves anyway - that sort of thing.

6. Generally gave it a bit of a TURBO BOOST, it was already fast enough on
LOCAL logins, but it was a bit "sluggish" when remote users accessed it.

7. Included "Filesizes" so users can see at a glance just how much stuff
they have flagged for download!



                               Version 1.4.1
                               -------------

IMPORTANT - This is on Amiga Format CD 44 - DO NOT USE IT, IT IS BUGGED AND
WILL FAIL TO DOWNLOAD!!!!!!  Get 1.4.2 From The Aminet or use 1.5 instead.


Erm, for some strange reason (ie, I "fixed" it online then sent it 2 a user
who sent it to another user....  then I realised that I'd only "clodge"
fixed it and it probably WOULD work, but I had better be damn sure) - there
are THREE different version 1.4.1 floating about.

There's 1.4.1 - the "original" version
1.4.1 (bug fix) - which is the "clodge" version I fixed online for a user,
and there's 1.4.1 (BUG FIX) - which may have been leaked out due to a sysop
access user accessing the CLI on my BBS whilst I was out and grabbing it.


Anyway - here's the docs for this version....

Important NEWS!!!  This version has been "Bug-fixed".  I put a NEW routine
in which is capable of downloading files with "extra" spaces at the end of
them.  However, like a complete TOOL I used th same "space" adding code at
Download stage.  This sadly meant the ORINIGAL 1.4.1 COULD NOT DOWNLOAD
ANYTHING!!!!  This version has been BUG-FIXED!!!!  (Thanks to Dunkie from
Quest BBS for spotting this bug)

1. Seperated the files and filesize display to give ANOTHER 50% speed
increase when using the door "remotely". (No need to continously update the
filesize display if you are simply scrolling up and down the filelist - it 
now "updates" only when you perform a PAGE command) 

2. Removed all screen "section" blanking code, and replaced it with
enhanced "intellegent" routines, capable of deciding if and when they
should blank off various sections.  Works out how far down the screen they
are - and deletes only neccessary lines.

3. Rewritten PAGE forwards and reverse code to take advantage of the
smarter screen refresh routine.

4. All ANSI positioning, colour issuing and screen clearing commands are now 
done in ANSI rather than parsing variables to and from routines, results in 
much smaller executable filesize, and a slight speed up at run time.

5. Now able to "download" files which have SPACES after the filename.  As
far as I'm aware - this is the ONLY CD Door which can do this!!! (KewlCDPro
just exists without attempting to get the files - tested on KewlCDPro 1.6)




                               Version 1.4.2
                               -------------


1.  Fixed "proper" the clodge from version 1.4.1 (bug fix) which meant the
download part worked if files had spaces in them.

2. Figured out that Max doesn't like spaces BETWEEN words (ie, it won't let
you download the buggers, even though I had managed to "grab" them to the
temporary directory.

2.1 Sorted that out by "cheating" and swapping any "space" characters for a
"_" character!!  Called for a re-write of a the MARK/UNMARK code so it was
intelligent enough to swap back and forth between what it KNEW the filename
was Ie "Barbie Girl" - and what was on disk ie, "Barbie_Girl")

3. Removed massive chunks of code which "removed" spaces from the strings
after a DIR FIRST or DIR NEXT, because Max's doesn't care if there are
spaces at the end of strings and will download them quite happily



                                Version 1.5
                                -----------

1. Increased number of files per directory limit AND directory limit ITSELF
from 512 to 1024....

2. Now able to show ALL files regardless of how BIG they are (fixes a
BIZZARE error in 1.4.2 whereby files over 96MEG resulted in an error)

3. NEW!!!  File Comment Support - File Comments are displayed in the BLUE
ANSI line at the bottom of the screen

4. Search feature.  Totally MARKABLE for easy downloading.  Can store upto
1024 "matched" entries in the list and MARK the same amount.

5. Fixed a weird bug which stopped the door from Downloading files/dirs
with TILD signs in them....

6. MUTLIPLE CD/ZIP aware.  Important - See the @{"Limitations" link Limitations} Section.

7. Creates an INDEX of the ENTIRE CD for use with the SEARCH feature.  
The index is created AUTOMATICALLY if it doesn't exist - the 1st time a user 
requests a search.  (One in the eye for Steve Clack...)

8. Now makes a logical ASSIGN to the CD path to enable accurate Downloading
EVERY time (there where STILL some weird instances where the door was
refusing to Download files from the CD).

9. Tidys up after itself - deletes FOUND FILES LISTS, removes ASSIGNS etc -
very user friendly.



                               Version 1.5r1
                               -------------


1. Altered the keyfile routine.  Studidly two positions within the key
where erroring and generating a nice DIVISION BY ZERO problem.  No current
keys are affected unless you had a REALLY long sysop name!!



                             @{"MAIN MENU" Link MAIN}


@endnode
@node NEW "What's New"
---<What's New>---

                               Version 1.5r2
                               -------------

1. Fixed yet ANOTHER bug related to the multi-changer routine.  Basically
the routine would fail if one device in the chain was missing (ie if you
told it to start from CD0:, then only actually put disks in CD1: upwards it
would fail)

2. Also - changed the way it handles the multi-changer bit, as it got all
confused if CD1: was in link 0 etc, all fixed now :-)

3. Added a "VIEW file_id.diz" routine to the MAIN program section
(actually, I could incorporate it into the FOUND routine as well, but this
would require a COMPLETE RE-WRITE so I'll leave it alone, as I'm sick of
this door now....)

4. Keyfile routine STILL reads your existing FrillyCDPro.Key and will use
it, however - if you DON'T possess one, your copy is STILL registered and
will say "REGISTERED to: The BBS Community"

This door is 100% FREE!!!! - All source code is included (Keyfile routine
has been removed from public released source code version - however it's
STILL a registered version....)




Also see the @{"History" Link HISTORY} Section...




                             @{"MAIN MENU" Link MAIN}


@endnode
@node LIMITATIONS "Limitations"
---<Limitations of the Door>---



                Limitations of the Door
                -----------------------

1. I have a MOD collection CD from Finland which has been mastered on an
Apple Mac.  One of the directories is: "AC/DC" - yup, a directory with a "/"
character in it.  Basically, the door CANNOT even get inside this drawer 
(try it with Directory Opus, this can't do it either).  Also - my PC owning
mate tried, and failed to access the directory using his PC!!  So all in all, 
I think it's pretty water tight.

2. For the CD-Changer to work - your drives MUST be named CONSECUTIVELY ie
CD0:, CD1:, CD2: and NOT "A:", "B:" like on a PC....  This is STAYING as it
is - people will just HAVE to be more sensible naming there devices ;-)





                             @{"MAIN MENU" Link MAIN}


@endnode
